**Key Differences:**

- **C-8 vs. C-7:** The C-8 introduces external antennas, built-in Wi-Fi, USB-C, Zigbee 3.0, Z-Wave 800 with Long Range support, and enhanced Matter compatibility, offering better range and future-proofing over the C-7.îˆ†

- **C-8 Pro vs. C-8:** The C-8 Pro upgrades to a faster ARM Cortex-A55 processor and doubles the RAM to 2 GB, resulting in approximately 50% faster performance and improved handling of large device networks and complex automations. îˆ€citeîˆ‚turn0search5îˆîˆ†

**Considerations:**

- If you have a small to medium setup and are budget-conscious, the **C-7** remains a viable option.îˆ†

- For enhanced range, built-in Wi-Fi, and better protocol support, the **C-8** is suitable for most users.îˆ†

- If you require higher performance for extensive device networks or complex automations, the **C-8 Pro** is the optimal choice.îˆ†

**Migration:**

Hubitat provides a migration tool to facilitate moving from older models to newer ones, including transferring Z-Wave and Zigbee devices. Note that migrating from a newer model to an older one (e.g., C-8 Pro to C-8) may require a Hub Protect subscription. îˆ€citeîˆ‚turn0search5îˆîˆ†

